WEBVTT

00:02.102 --> 00:06.038
[Randy] No, Earl. You're not listening.
I never said "instead of."

00:06.139 --> 00:08.039
You'd still have
your regular hands...

00:08.141 --> 00:10.109
but you'd <i>also</i> have robot hands.

00:10.210 --> 00:13.941
Okay, fine. Yes, and with robot hands,
you could open beers faster.

00:14.047 --> 00:15.947
Thank you. Geez.

00:16.049 --> 00:19.246
- Oh, wow. Look, a hat.
- Randy, wait!

00:19.352 --> 00:21.513
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>Every now and then, Randy found a new hat-</i>

00:21.621 --> 00:23.680
<i>which brought the unwelcome</i>
<i>addition oflice...</i>

00:23.790 --> 00:26.020
<i>and a new personality.</i>

00:26.126 --> 00:28.686
[Mexican Accent]
Let's go get some chicken wings!

00:30.363 --> 00:33.332
[Imitating John Wayne]
Howdy, pilgrim.

00:33.433 --> 00:36.266
Yo, yo, yo!
What's up, my home-Earl?

00:36.369 --> 00:38.200
<i>But Randy hadn't found a hat</i>
<i>in a while...</i>

00:38.304 --> 00:40.898
<i>and I was hopin'this time</i>
<i>would be different.</i>

00:41.007 --> 00:43.134
- Hey, Earl.
- Yeah?

00:43.243 --> 00:45.939
Wouldst thou fancy a beer?
I certainly shall.

00:46.980 --> 00:49.881
- Son of a bitch.
- Don't dally.

00:51.751 --> 00:54.311
<i>My name is Earl.</i>

00:58.458 --> 01:00.824
Darnell, I do believe I'll have a beer-
in a glass.

01:00.927 --> 01:03.327
And you know what,
why don't we throw a cherry on top.

01:05.364 --> 01:07.265
Thank you, my fine sir.

01:07.367 --> 01:09.267
Oh, so suave.

01:09.369 --> 01:12.065
- I feel like I'm in Rick's Caf� Am�ricain.
- [Chuckles]

01:13.506 --> 01:14.939
<i>Casablanca.</i>

01:15.041 --> 01:16.941
They don't watch
black-and-white movies...

01:17.043 --> 01:19.011
'cause it reminds them too much
of newspapers.

01:19.112 --> 01:21.342
They don't watch
black-and-white movies...

01:21.448 --> 01:23.939
because it reminds <i>whom</i>
too much of newspapers.

01:24.050 --> 01:27.747
Now, if you'll excuse me,
therefore, what for...

01:27.854 --> 01:30.982
wherewithal, henceforth,
English muffins.

01:31.091 --> 01:33.821
[Sighs]

01:33.927 --> 01:37.226
I seen the giant pig!
I seen Pigsquatch!

01:37.330 --> 01:39.321
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>There was a legend of a giant pig...</i>

01:39.432 --> 01:41.457
<i>that lived in the woods</i>
<i>near the trailer park.</i>

01:41.568 --> 01:43.832
<i>Nobody sober had ever</i>
<i>actually seen it-</i>

01:43.937 --> 01:46.770
- <i>[Grunting, Squealing]</i>
- [Gasps] Pigsquatch!

01:46.873 --> 01:49.933
- <i>until Joy.</i>
- Pigsquatch.

01:50.043 --> 01:53.809
You sure the neighbor didn't just wheel his
shut-in mom out to the yard to hose her off?

01:53.913 --> 01:58.748
I think I know the difference
between a prehistoric pig and Jumbo Sally.

01:58.852 --> 02:01.844
You know what I'm gonna do?
I'm gonna catch him.

02:01.955 --> 02:04.014
Joy, what would you do
with a giant pig?

02:04.124 --> 02:07.218
Make a damn fortune.
Tourists pay good money to see giant stuff.

02:07.327 --> 02:09.521
World's biggest Slinky.
World's biggest staircase-

02:09.628 --> 02:11.529
which is next
to the world's biggest Slinky.

02:11.631 --> 02:14.532
Even me and this idiot paid 10 bucks each
to see the world's biggest anthill.

02:14.634 --> 02:16.932
Remember that-
when we took that R.V. Trip?

02:17.036 --> 02:18.936
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>I did remember.</i>

02:19.038 --> 02:22.132
<i>'Cause that R. V. Trip she was talking about</i>
<i>was number 47 on my list.</i>

02:22.242 --> 02:26.042
<i>A while back, the kids were mistakenly</i>
<i>detained by Child Protective Services.</i>

02:26.146 --> 02:28.046
<i>Since we knew</i>
<i>they were in good hands...</i>

02:28.148 --> 02:30.116
<i>we decided we wanted</i>
<i>to go on vacation.</i>

02:30.216 --> 02:32.241
- <i>So we stole one.</i>
- [Engine Starts]

02:32.352 --> 02:36.880
<i>#And when I wanna go home</i>
<i>I'm goin'mobile #</i>

02:36.990 --> 02:39.652
<i>And we discovered we hadn't</i>
<i>just stole a vacation...</i>

02:39.759 --> 02:42.057
<i>we stole a whole new lifestyle.</i>

02:42.162 --> 02:44.062
Check it out.

02:44.164 --> 02:46.394
These R.V. People
have special glasses just for wine.

02:46.499 --> 02:48.626
Wow. It looks like it's on stilts.

02:48.735 --> 02:51.898
That's really smart. It's closer to your mouth
so you can drink it faster.

02:52.005 --> 02:53.905
Man, R.V.'s are so much better
than trailers.

02:54.007 --> 02:55.998
When a twister's comin',
you can just drive away...

02:56.109 --> 02:59.306
instead of just sittin' in your bathtub
with a pillow over your head like a chump.

02:59.412 --> 03:02.040
- [Chuckles] I ain't ever goin' back.
- Don't have to.

03:02.148 --> 03:05.549
We're R.V. People now,
thanks to this baby.

03:05.652 --> 03:08.746
It's gonna be stilt glasses,
cup holders on the walls...

03:08.855 --> 03:11.881
and tables that turn into beds
from now on.

03:11.991 --> 03:14.152
Cheers to hittin' the freakin'jackpot.

03:19.132 --> 03:22.863
[Sighs] Randy, did you turn off the stove
when you were finished cookin' the Helper?

03:22.969 --> 03:26.632
Yeah. I mean, my hands were full,
so I blew it out.

03:26.739 --> 03:28.639
Lfigured, "What's the worst
that could happen?"

03:28.741 --> 03:30.732
Now we know.

03:30.843 --> 03:34.609
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>Andjust like that, our R. V.'ing days were over.</i>

03:34.714 --> 03:38.707
<i>Luckily, the guy we stole it from was living</i>
<i>in the same spot, just without wheels.</i>

03:38.818 --> 03:41.480
There's gotta be something
I can do for you-

03:41.588 --> 03:45.046
get you a new R.V.,
find you a new place to live.

03:45.158 --> 03:47.092
I don't want nothin'.
Just leave me alone...

03:47.193 --> 03:49.218
and let me sit here and wait to die.

03:49.329 --> 03:51.627
But I gotta cross you off my list.

03:51.731 --> 03:53.665
You wanna cross me off your list...

03:53.766 --> 03:57.566
just pump me full of morphine and beat me
over the head with that rake till I'm dead.

04:01.841 --> 04:05.368
<i>[Earl Narrating] I wasn't gonna kill the guy,</i>
<i>but I wasn't gonna do nothing either.</i>

04:05.478 --> 04:08.777
<i>So I decided to watch him</i>
<i>and see if I came up with any ideas.</i>

04:08.881 --> 04:12.840
- <i>## [Cowbell]</i>
- <i># All our times have come #</i>

04:14.287 --> 04:16.187
<i>And I found out he wasn't lying.</i>

04:16.289 --> 04:19.781
- <i># Here but now they're gone #</i>
- <i>He</i> was <i>just waiting to die.</i>

04:22.629 --> 04:25.189
<i>#Seasons don't fear the reaper#</i>

04:25.298 --> 04:29.166
<i>#Nor do the wind and the sun and the rain</i>
<i>We can be like they are #</i>

04:29.269 --> 04:32.966
- <i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>
- <i>While I still didn't know</i>
<i>what I was supposed to do to help him...</i>

04:33.072 --> 04:34.972
<i>at least I figured out</i>
<i>a place to start.</i>

04:35.074 --> 04:37.042
Mornin', Jerry.
I'm here to fix your roo-

04:37.143 --> 04:39.008
<i>#We'll be able to fly</i>
<i>Don't fear the reaper##</i>

04:39.112 --> 04:41.876
- Sorry.
- Doesn't matter.

04:43.583 --> 04:45.244
<i>While I was fixin'Jerry's roof...</i>

04:45.351 --> 04:48.809
<i>Joy was gettin'started</i>
<i>on her get-rich-quick pig plan.</i>

04:48.921 --> 04:52.618
- Baby, the boys are hungry. Where's the bacon?
- On the end of this string.

04:52.725 --> 04:54.625
Soon as Pigsquatch
gets a whiff of it...

04:54.727 --> 04:56.627
I'm gonna pull the string,
lure him to me...

04:56.729 --> 04:58.822
and then knock him out
with a baseball bat- kablam!

04:58.931 --> 05:00.831
You can't catch a pig with bacon.

05:00.933 --> 05:03.493
That's like trying to catch a cow
with a cheeseburger.

05:03.603 --> 05:06.265
Darnell, I'm hearin' a lot of"no" and "can't"
from you right now.

05:06.372 --> 05:08.966
If you're not gonna get with
the pig-catchin' program, shut the hell up.

05:09.075 --> 05:12.476
All I'm sayin' is the boys are drinking
Tom Collins mix for breakfast.

05:12.578 --> 05:16.309
We can't send 'em
to school like that.

05:16.416 --> 05:18.077
- <i>[Loud Grunt]</i>
- Jesus!

05:18.184 --> 05:20.084
<i>## [Radio: Country]</i>

05:20.186 --> 05:22.313
<i>[Earl Narrating] Although</i>
<i>I'd spent the morning fixing Jerry's roof...</i>

05:22.422 --> 05:24.481
<i>I couldn't help feeling</i>
<i>that I still hadn't done enough.</i>

05:24.590 --> 05:27.184
- [Changing Stations]
- At least it shouldn't rain on you anymore, huh?

05:27.293 --> 05:30.660
Let me get that for you.

05:31.998 --> 05:35.957
<i>## [Radio: Folk, Up-tempo]</i>

05:40.673 --> 05:42.732
<i>[Changing Stations]</i>

05:46.045 --> 05:49.742
- [Changing Stations]
- Wait. R-Randy, go back a station.

05:49.849 --> 05:52.682
## [Folk, Up-tempo]

05:56.522 --> 06:00.424
Jerry, you-you're movin'.
You like that jug music?

06:00.526 --> 06:03.393
Love the jug.

06:03.496 --> 06:06.021
It's the easiest instrument
to learn...

06:06.132 --> 06:08.726
hardest to master.

06:08.835 --> 06:10.735
Actually, that's not true.

06:10.837 --> 06:13.567
Hell, in a good wind,
it actually plays itself.

06:13.673 --> 06:16.938
You could be dead
for all that jug cares.

06:18.378 --> 06:20.278
I miss my jug.

06:20.380 --> 06:23.508
Used to have one
before you blew it up in that R.V. Fire...

06:23.616 --> 06:25.880
you jackass.

06:25.985 --> 06:28.818
<i>[Earl Narrating] It still didn't seem</i>
<i>like it made up for burning an R. V...</i>

06:28.921 --> 06:33.483
<i>but at least fixing his roof and getting him</i>
<i>a jug were better than doing nothin'.</i>

06:33.593 --> 06:36.790
Oh. That is a beauty.

06:36.896 --> 06:39.421
Brings back good memories, huh?

06:39.532 --> 06:41.591
Oh, yeah.

06:41.701 --> 06:44.226
My R.V. Was filled with memories.

06:44.337 --> 06:48.068
Doohickeys, things from my past-
you know, "momentos."

06:48.174 --> 06:50.665
Yep. The Freshmaker.

06:50.777 --> 06:53.302
Well, that's what I can do
to make up to you, Jerry-

06:53.413 --> 06:56.746
find some way to replace the things
that got burned up in your R.V.

06:56.849 --> 07:00.114
- What other stuff did you have in there?
- My dead wife.

07:00.219 --> 07:03.620
No, I don't think so. We probably
would've remembered a dead wife.

07:03.723 --> 07:05.782
No. Pictures of her.

07:05.892 --> 07:09.293
I had pictures of her
all over the wall.

07:09.395 --> 07:13.798
Yeah, l- I met her when I first came back
from the war in Korea.

07:13.900 --> 07:17.666
<i>Those pictures kinda made me feel</i>
<i>like her arms were around me.</i>

07:18.938 --> 07:22.499
This was her song-
"Moonlight Sonata."

07:24.043 --> 07:26.705
## [Single Note]

07:26.813 --> 07:31.216
## [Repeating Same Note]

07:44.063 --> 07:47.032
## [Same, Long Note]

07:52.238 --> 07:55.230
And that, gentlemen,
will get you laid.

07:55.341 --> 07:57.935
<i>[Earl Narrating] I didn't know how</i>
<i>to replace pictures ofJerry's dead wife...</i>

07:58.044 --> 08:01.309
<i>but ifhe needed some arms around him,</i>
<i>I had an idea where to go.</i>

08:02.748 --> 08:04.739
That's a good one.

08:04.851 --> 08:07.820
My favorite is still the one
where you're riding it sidesaddle.

08:07.920 --> 08:11.378
Acting ladylike on a giant pig-
That makes me laugh.

08:11.491 --> 08:14.221
Just keep takin' pictures
before this thing wakes up.

08:14.327 --> 08:17.387
Holy crap!
You caught Pigsquatch?

08:17.497 --> 08:20.989
- How'd you do it?
- Put a bunch of sleeping pills in a bucket of slop-

08:21.100 --> 08:23.364
basically the pig version
of how I got you to marry me.

08:23.469 --> 08:26.029
Nice. Listen, do you still
have that Real Doll...

08:26.138 --> 08:28.129
you bought to make Darnell
think you were in bed...

08:28.241 --> 08:30.141
when you ran to Mexico
to avoid the cops...

08:30.243 --> 08:32.472
but got caught by Dog,
the bounty hunter, went on trial...

08:32.578 --> 08:35.410
and I went to prison for it,
then got out, got hit by a car...

08:35.515 --> 08:38.506
and went into a coma where I thought
I was livin' in a sitcom world?

08:38.618 --> 08:41.381
- Yeah.
- Can I take her? It's for a good cause.

08:41.486 --> 08:45.287
I don't know. Me and Darnell still use her
sometimes on date night.

08:46.626 --> 08:48.924
Boys, Mommy and Daddy are goin' out.

08:49.028 --> 08:50.689
<i>Aunt Gretchen's here to babysit.</i>

08:50.796 --> 08:54.391
And if I were you, I'd stay in your room,
'cause she brought her paddle.

08:56.068 --> 08:59.162
Okay, baby,
let's go eat some shrimps.

09:04.544 --> 09:06.808
You know what-
if you want her, you can have her.

09:06.913 --> 09:09.108
Caught Darnell takin' a bath with her
the other day.

09:09.215 --> 09:11.615
Says he was washing her.
I have my doubts.

09:11.717 --> 09:13.617
Thanks, Joy.

09:15.488 --> 09:18.753
Joy, come here.
Does this pig look funny to you?

09:18.858 --> 09:20.758
All pigs look funny to me, Darnell.

09:20.860 --> 09:24.057
Porky, Petunia, Miss Piggy-
hilarious.

09:24.163 --> 09:26.996
No, I mean in that it's not breathing.
He's dead.

09:27.099 --> 09:29.499
And I don't think anybody's gonna pay
to see a dead pig.

09:29.602 --> 09:32.298
He's not dead.
He's just sleeping.

09:34.507 --> 09:37.738
Oh, hell.
I only gave him 50 pills.

09:37.843 --> 09:41.472
My mama used to take that many every
Friday night and wash it down with a gin Rickey...

09:41.581 --> 09:44.914
and wake up the next morning
feeling fresh as a daisy to do her paper route.

09:45.017 --> 09:47.247
Damn lightweight.

09:47.486 --> 09:49.977
- ## [Note Repeating]
- <i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>Once I got the Real Doll from Joy...</i>

09:50.089 --> 09:54.082
<i>me and Randy gave it a makeover</i>
<i>and changed it into a Real Old Doll.</i>

09:54.193 --> 09:57.424
Hey, Jerry, check it out.
Arms to put around you.

10:00.600 --> 10:03.592
What good is a plastic mannequin
gonna do me?

10:03.703 --> 10:05.603
Give it a shot.

10:08.140 --> 10:10.267
Can you make the hug tighter?

10:10.376 --> 10:12.344
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>After he got the doll...</i>

10:12.445 --> 10:16.575
<i>Jerry started thinking about more things</i>
<i>from his trailer that he wanted us to replace-</i>

10:16.682 --> 10:18.616
[Chuckling]
Hey, did you have fun?

10:18.718 --> 10:21.118
<i>Like his old animal heads.</i>

10:21.220 --> 10:22.915
<i>#I'm alive #</i>

10:23.022 --> 10:26.116
<i>And the more stuff we replaced,</i>
<i>like his old hunting equipment...</i>

10:26.225 --> 10:29.388
<i>the more alive he became.</i>

10:29.495 --> 10:32.987
<i>By the time we tracked down an exact</i>
<i>replica ofhis Special Forces uniform...</i>

10:33.099 --> 10:34.828
<i>he was a new man.</i>

10:34.934 --> 10:37.903
<i>#Is this really me ##</i>

10:38.004 --> 10:40.996
<i>And he was feelin'so good,</i>
<i>he even wanted to go out for a drink.</i>

10:41.107 --> 10:42.802
[Laughing]

10:42.908 --> 10:45.206
Oh, there's one more thing I need.
It's a pendant.

10:45.311 --> 10:48.974
There's only one other like it
in the whole wide world.

10:49.081 --> 10:51.379
An old army buddy of mine has it...

10:51.484 --> 10:53.679
and I would like
to go with you to get it.

10:53.786 --> 10:57.813
- That's the spirit.
- Yes. Hip, hip. Cheerios. Harry Potter.

10:57.923 --> 11:00.858
[Laughing]
Huh?

11:00.960 --> 11:03.019
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>I was feeling good.</i>

11:03.129 --> 11:05.893
<i>I hadn't given up on Jerry,</i>
<i>and it paid off.</i>

11:05.998 --> 11:08.592
<i>I really felt like</i>
<i>I brought a man back to life.</i>

11:12.238 --> 11:15.071
According to the V.F.W.,
this is the place.

11:16.108 --> 11:18.303
Oh, I wanna thank you, Earl.

11:20.946 --> 11:24.541
All I wanted to do was die.
Now look at me.

11:24.650 --> 11:29.019
I got my stuff back.
I got my plastic wife to hug.

11:29.121 --> 11:31.919
And now I'm gonna cut
this jackass's ear off.

11:33.225 --> 11:36.353
I can't thank you enough, Earl.

11:36.462 --> 11:38.396
Did you say cut off his ear?

11:41.899 --> 11:44.094
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

11:44.201 --> 11:46.761
You're gonna cut off
your army buddy's ear?

11:46.870 --> 11:49.236
Yeah. That's what the "pendant" was.
I'd have called it an ear...

11:49.339 --> 11:51.239
but you probably wouldn't
have driven me here.

11:51.341 --> 11:53.536
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>Ends up, during the Korean War...</i>

11:53.644 --> 11:57.478
<i>Jerry and his buddy were caught behind</i>
<i>enemy lines when Jerry got wounded.</i>

11:57.581 --> 11:59.481
- <i>[Machine Gun Fire]</i>
- [Groans]

11:59.583 --> 12:01.642
Jerry, we both can't make it.

12:01.752 --> 12:05.449
No, don't go. Haven't you seen the movies?
"Never leave a man behind."

12:05.556 --> 12:09.048
No, but I seen the ones
where they say, "Go on without me."

12:09.159 --> 12:11.059
Sometimes they even say,
"Marry my best girl."

12:11.161 --> 12:13.061
- Sorry!
- Damn you-

12:13.163 --> 12:16.394
<i>But the only thing Jerry</i>
<i>could keep from leaving was Joe's ear.</i>

12:16.500 --> 12:18.627
[Shrieking]

12:18.735 --> 12:20.635
Joe!

12:20.737 --> 12:22.637
Come back here, you coward!

12:22.739 --> 12:25.071
You're a coward!

12:25.175 --> 12:27.166
[Grunting]

12:27.277 --> 12:29.336
<i>Jerry got captured</i>
<i>and held on to the ear...</i>

12:29.446 --> 12:33.007
<i>as a reminder ofhow much</i>
<i>he wanted to survive.</i>

12:33.116 --> 12:36.051
<i>And as the months passed,</i>
<i>the ear became more than a reminder.</i>

12:36.153 --> 12:38.053
<i>It became a companion.</i>

12:38.155 --> 12:40.749
I got four pretty ladies.
What do you got, Joe's ear?

12:42.459 --> 12:44.586
Damn, Joe's ear.
You're good.

12:46.263 --> 12:49.630
<i>And it continued to be a part ofhis life</i>
<i>even after the war.</i>

12:49.733 --> 12:51.963
Okay, Isabel, Joe's ear...

12:52.069 --> 12:55.630
we're off to see the world.

12:59.076 --> 13:00.976
Sorry. I can't let you do this.

13:01.078 --> 13:02.978
I'm not asking for your permission.

13:03.080 --> 13:07.210
That coward left me for dead for 50 years,
and he never gave it another thought.

13:08.251 --> 13:11.015
Jerry, give me the knife.

13:14.825 --> 13:17.259
[Groans, Grunts]

13:18.328 --> 13:20.296
[Whimpers]

13:25.168 --> 13:27.068
[Earl]
Joe!

13:28.305 --> 13:30.398
Look out, Joe!

13:30.507 --> 13:32.407
Joe!

13:32.509 --> 13:34.443
What the hell's goin' on out here?

13:34.544 --> 13:36.910
- Jerry Burney's here for your ear.
- Jerry?

13:37.014 --> 13:39.983
[Gasping]

13:40.083 --> 13:42.142
[Choking]
I'm here to protect you from him.

13:42.252 --> 13:44.311
Where is he?

13:46.423 --> 13:48.823
[Coughing]

13:48.925 --> 13:51.723
<i>[Earl Narrating] After I got my voice back,</i>
<i>I told Joe about the R. V...</i>

13:51.828 --> 13:54.888
<i>and finding Jerry half dead</i>
<i>and what I'd been doing.</i>

13:56.733 --> 14:00.328
You idiots.
Do you know what you've done?

14:00.437 --> 14:03.338
You brought a killing machine
back to life.

14:03.440 --> 14:06.898
- [Groans]
- You okay?

14:07.010 --> 14:09.410
Heart pills!
Top pocket!

14:11.214 --> 14:14.843
Do you ever perchance think of gluing
a seashell to where your ear used to be...

14:14.951 --> 14:16.350
so it would look normal?

14:16.453 --> 14:19.513
And you'd always
get to hear the ocean.

14:19.623 --> 14:22.353
Yeah, that's-
That's my biggest problem right now.

14:22.459 --> 14:25.951
You guys don't seem to understand
what we're dealing with here.

14:27.397 --> 14:31.527
I saw Jerry kill three Koreans
with a single bullet.

14:32.602 --> 14:34.502
No gun.

14:34.604 --> 14:37.198
Just pressed the bullet
right into their skulls.

14:38.875 --> 14:40.900
I'm callin' the cops!

14:42.979 --> 14:45.573
- <i>[Taps Switch]</i>
- Damn.

14:45.682 --> 14:48.014
He cut the line.

14:48.118 --> 14:51.781
Well, he's not the only
crazy old man around here.

14:54.591 --> 14:57.526
- Oh, Mother!
- Blimey!

14:57.627 --> 15:00.960
H-H-Hey, J-J-Joe. Before we panic
and do something we might regret...

15:01.064 --> 15:02.964
at least let me talk toJerry.

15:03.066 --> 15:05.500
He seemed reasonable-
except for the throat punch.

15:05.602 --> 15:08.070
Oh. Okay. Let's see.

15:09.272 --> 15:11.172
Uh-
[Stammers]

15:13.844 --> 15:16.142
Hey, Jerry. I'm sorry
about what hap-

15:18.548 --> 15:21.847
Okay, boys, this is it.

15:21.952 --> 15:25.615
Cinch up your apple sacks.
We're goin' to war.

15:25.722 --> 15:29.214
<i>[Earl Narrating] And I wasn't the only one</i>
<i>dealing with a scary thing in the front yard.</i>

15:29.326 --> 15:33.023
<i>Since the pig didn't die of natural causes,</i>
<i>the county wouldn't haul it away.</i>

15:33.130 --> 15:36.258
I can't believe the county
won't remove dead pigs.

15:36.366 --> 15:39.767
I can't believe nobody answered our ad
for 800 pounds of free pork.

15:39.870 --> 15:42.703
You know what- screw it.

15:42.806 --> 15:45.274
I'm goin' old school.

15:45.375 --> 15:49.778
Yech! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God! Darnell!

15:49.880 --> 15:52.815
I'm in the pig!
I'm in the pig!

15:55.886 --> 15:58.116
Earl, this hat sucks now.
It's got a hole in it.

15:58.221 --> 16:01.315
- It looks like a hobo's hat.
- Randy, this really isn't the time.

16:01.424 --> 16:03.392
Joe, this is crazy.

16:03.493 --> 16:06.724
You don't have to kill each other over
something that happened 40 years ago.

16:06.830 --> 16:10.027
Learn your history!
It was 55 years ago.

16:10.133 --> 16:12.226
Pin! Pin! Pin!

16:12.335 --> 16:15.896
Oh, nuts.
Man, I'm shaking like a geisha on sake.

16:16.006 --> 16:18.566
It must be the Parkinson's.
You better do it.

16:18.675 --> 16:21.269
Earl. Earl, we gotta go
back to that bus stop...

16:21.378 --> 16:23.369
and see if they got
another hat like this one.

16:23.480 --> 16:25.380
Randy, I'm defusing a grenade.

16:25.482 --> 16:27.382
I can't wear this.
I'll look stupid.

16:27.484 --> 16:29.918
Randy, you're gonna look stupid anyway.
It's a stupid hat.

16:30.020 --> 16:32.011
Just like all your
other hats are stupid...

16:32.122 --> 16:34.454
'cause when you wear a hat,
you act stupid.

16:34.558 --> 16:37.254
- Even the newsie cap?
- Yes, the newsie cap!

16:37.360 --> 16:39.351
[Cockney Accent]
"Eh, mister. Want a paper?"

16:39.462 --> 16:41.726
"I'll have a sandwich
with extra mayonnaise."

16:41.832 --> 16:43.732
[Normal Voice]
I hate all your hats.

16:43.834 --> 16:46.428
Will you guys shut up and put the-
Put the pin in!

16:48.438 --> 16:50.338
[Sighs]

16:52.442 --> 16:54.342
[Exhales]

16:54.444 --> 16:56.344
Man, I don't believe you two guys.

16:56.446 --> 16:58.573
Arguin' over a hat.
A damn hat!

16:58.682 --> 17:01.276
I'm gonna get killed
because there's a lunatic out there...

17:01.384 --> 17:04.079
who's mad as hell
because I left him in the field.

17:04.186 --> 17:06.621
L-

17:06.723 --> 17:08.917
I left him in the field.

17:09.025 --> 17:10.925
My best buddy.

17:11.027 --> 17:14.053
He needed my help, and-
and I left him.

17:14.164 --> 17:16.064
I left him.

17:16.165 --> 17:19.101
<i>[Earl Narrating] That was the fi</i> r <i>st time</i>
<i>Joe ever said those words out loud...</i>

17:19.202 --> 17:21.568
<i>but been in his head</i>
<i>since the day it happened.</i>

17:21.671 --> 17:24.265
- <i>[Machine Gun Fire]</i>
- <i>He'd gone off to war hoping to be a hero...</i>

17:24.374 --> 17:27.275
- <i>but quickly found out he was just a scared kid.</i>
- <i>[Shell Incoming]</i>

17:31.214 --> 17:34.377
<i>Jerry felt thatJoe ran away</i>
<i>and never gave it a second thought.</i>

17:34.484 --> 17:36.384
<i>ButJerry was wrong.</i>

17:36.486 --> 17:39.250
<i>Joe thought about it</i>
<i>every day ofhis life.</i>

17:39.356 --> 17:42.120
<i>[Jerry's Voice]</i>
<i>Joe! Come back here, you coward!</i>

17:42.225 --> 17:45.217
<i>You're a coward!</i>

17:45.328 --> 17:49.196
When I was given the choice
to save my life or save someone else's...

17:49.299 --> 17:51.494
I chose to save my own.

17:51.601 --> 17:53.831
MaybeJerry deserves
to take the other ear.

17:53.937 --> 17:58.499
Hell, I'd give it to him, too,
if I didn't remember it hurt so damn much.

17:58.608 --> 18:00.735
How much did it hurt?

18:00.844 --> 18:03.438
Oh, about as much
as getting your ear cut off.

18:03.546 --> 18:05.070
[No Audible Dialogue]

18:05.181 --> 18:07.342
- <i>[Loud Thud]</i>
- Oh, God! He's on the roof!

18:07.450 --> 18:09.475
W-W-Wait!
Joe, wait!

18:09.586 --> 18:12.783
- <i>[Gunfi</i> r <i>e]</i>
- <i>[Object Clattering]</i>

18:18.428 --> 18:20.919
Maybe we should call an ambulance.

18:21.765 --> 18:24.097
Or that.

18:25.936 --> 18:27.927
Oh, my God!
You killed his wife.

18:28.038 --> 18:30.472
Now he's really gonna be pissed.

18:30.573 --> 18:33.269
Quick. Back in the house.
Come on!

18:37.547 --> 18:39.447
<i>[Creaking]</i>

18:39.549 --> 18:41.312
- Ear!
- [All Screaming]

18:41.418 --> 18:43.545
- Aha!
- <i>[Joe Whimpering]</i>

18:43.653 --> 18:46.121
<i>Jerry may have had</i>
<i>the heart of a killer...</i>

18:46.222 --> 18:48.486
<i>but that heart was 75 years old.</i>

18:48.591 --> 18:51.788
[Groaning, Gasping]

18:53.997 --> 18:56.625
I think he's having a heart attack.
Randy, go for help.

18:56.733 --> 18:59.361
- <i>[Jerry, Gasping]Joe?</i>
- Joe, I need your pills.

18:59.469 --> 19:02.302
- [Gasping]
- Both of you?

19:02.405 --> 19:05.966
<i>This should be a lesson about trying</i>
<i>to kill people when you're over 60.</i>

19:07.811 --> 19:10.575
I only got one pill left.

19:12.983 --> 19:16.248
- [Groaning]
- Wh-What are you doin'?

19:16.353 --> 19:19.015
<i>What I should have done</i>
<i>50 years ago.</i>

19:19.122 --> 19:20.817
[Groaning]

19:20.924 --> 19:23.051
Open your mouth, you old buzzard.

19:25.862 --> 19:29.161
"Never leave a man behind."
[Groans]

19:29.265 --> 19:32.200
<i>[Siren Approaching]</i>

19:32.302 --> 19:35.203
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>In the end, they both survived.</i>

19:35.305 --> 19:38.399
It's okay.
You saved my life...

19:38.508 --> 19:40.499
so we're even.

19:40.610 --> 19:42.578
That's a load off my mind.

19:45.849 --> 19:48.147
<i>While you can't reattach</i>
<i>a severed ear...</i>

19:48.251 --> 19:50.685
<i>it's never too late</i>
<i>to fix a severed friendship.</i>

19:55.725 --> 19:57.886
<i>Losing your temper</i>
<i>can be a good thing.</i>

19:57.994 --> 20:01.225
<i>Jerry and Joe had let their bad feelings</i>
<i>sit inside them for years...</i>

20:01.331 --> 20:03.492
<i>rot like a pig in a front yard.</i>

20:03.600 --> 20:05.568
<i>And it took a fight</i>
<i>to work everything out.</i>

20:05.668 --> 20:07.568
<i>The same with me and Randy.</i>

20:07.670 --> 20:10.195
Hey, Earl. Thanks for telling me
I acted different in hats.

20:10.306 --> 20:12.206
I won't do it again.
I promise.

20:12.308 --> 20:14.242
I'm just sorry I yelled at you.

20:14.344 --> 20:16.574
Oh, that's okay.
Brothers fight.

20:16.679 --> 20:18.579
Friends cut each other's ears off.

20:18.681 --> 20:20.581
It's a crazy world, Earl.

20:20.683 --> 20:22.583
Well, I guess this is good-bye.

20:26.890 --> 20:28.881
It can make anyone look good.

20:28.992 --> 20:31.324
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>I guess, every now and then, when you're stuck...</i>

20:31.428 --> 20:34.488
<i>best way to clear the air</i>
<i>is to have a big blowup.</i>

20:34.597 --> 20:37.157
Fire in the hog!

20:39.369 --> 20:41.462
- [Crowd Cheering]
- [Man] Yeah!
